                "name": "Rowan Thomas",
                "href": "/profile/Rowan-Thomas-33"
            },
            "answer_text": "Absolutely! It\u2019s important for minority characters to be included in current media, and as long as you do your research on what it is like to be nonbinary/agender, it\u2019s perfectly fine! Now, do remember that you have to do research. A cis person may not notice if you don\u2019t, but trans and nonbinary people will be able to tell within seconds whether or not you took the time to learn The best way to make a minority character (or any character, really) is to start by making a character, then add features. Don\u2019t make an agender character, make a character who, for example, enjoys painting and aspires to be an artist, who happens to also be agender Good luck! ",
